  {
    "client_msg_id": "2dfd238f-0883-4af8-ba6a-8473e7eb3229",
    "type": "message",
    "text": "I think this line of thinking fits the constructivist/constructionist paradigm really well: you can never simply import new ideas into your brain. You can only build new brain structures out of existing brain structures, which is the essence of analogy/metaphor: illustrating one thing in terms of other things",
    "user": "U5TCAFTD3",
    "ts": "1543579275.003100",
