  {
    "client_msg_id": "ed0b862e-4ea6-4350-8b99-f8f9551dbf15",
    "type": "message",
    "text": "Very interesting topic. One implication is we almost always misunderstand stuff, specially newer ideas - because we'll see things from our existing context instead of the context of the originator. Reminded me of the quotes \"We don’t see things as they are, we see them as we are\" and \"I'll see it when I believe it\".",
