  {
    "client_msg_id": "52155a4e-95e3-44b0-a7fc-1844046331d1",
    "type": "message",
    "text": "I think that 'different representations of essentially the same information' is really the deeper problem and having better models for each of those representations isn't going to get us where we want to be. Shuffling data between the db model, rpc model, language types model while mentally reasoning about consistency is just tedious busywork.",
